EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to the Public Employees’ Benefits Program;
requiring the Board of the Public Employees’ Benefits
Program to report certain information relating to the costs
of health insurance for certain retirees; revising provisions
relating to the subsidy paid for certain health and welfare
benefits for certain state employees who have retired with
state service; revising requirements for certain retired
public officers and employees to reinstate insurance under
the Program; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Office of Finance to establish an assessment to pay
2 for a portion of the costs of the premiums or contributions for the Public
3 Employees’ Benefits Program on behalf of persons who were initially hired before
4 January 1, 2012, and have retired with state service, which must be: (1) deposited in
5 the State Retirees’ Health and Welfare Benefits Fund to pay a portion of the current
6 and future health and welfare benefits of those retirees; and (2) based upon a base
7 amount approved by the Legislature each session. Existing law also requires that,
8 for retirees who receive health coverage through Medicare, the portion paid to the
9 Program from the Retirees’ Fund on behalf of these retirees must be: (1) for
10 persons who retired before January 1, 1994, the base funding level defined by the
11 Legislature multiplied by 15; and (2) for persons who retired on or after January 1,
12 1994, the base funding level multiplied by the years of service of the person,
13 excluding service purchased, up to a maximum of 20 years. (NRS 287.046) Section
14 1 of this bill requires the Board of the Program to report, before August 31 of every
15 even-numbered year, to the Governor and the Interim Retirement and Benefits
